To move the project to GitHub from the system:
1- Go to the project folder with the cd nameProject command
2- Git the project with the git init command
3- Add files with the git add -A or git add command.
4- Commit changes with the git commit -m "message…." command
5- Rename the branch with the git branch -M main command
6- Connect the project to the Git repository with the git remote add origin repositoryAddress command
7- Note: The repository we created in GitHub has an address link that we use in step 6
8- Check with the git remote -v command
9- Send the project to Git with the main git push -u origin command
10- Note: If we do not do step 5, we are actually in the master branch and command 9 will not work.


If the GitHub repository address is not correct, we remove the address with the following command: git remote remove origin .
And we re-run the modified address to add the repository with the command: git remote add origin address git project .
Now, after modifying the GitHub repository address, we move it to the master branch with the command: git push -u origin master .


