Creating a new branch to apply changes to the project: 
1- First, we bring the project using the two methods mentioned in the terminal
2- We create a branch with the command nameBranch git branch 
3- To know which branch we are on, the command git branch
4- Command 3 shows that we are on the main branch
5- Now we go to the new branch with the command git checkout nameBranch
6- We repeat command 3, which shows that we are on the new branch
7- Now we can create, modify, delete files, and ...
8- Now to return to the main branch, the command git checkout main 
9- And we merge the new branch with the main branch with the command git merge nameBranch
10- To delete branches or branches, the command git branch -d nameBranch


When two people are working on the same branch:
Scenario 1: Two people working directly on the `main` branch:
1-	Fetch the latest changes from the repository: `git pull origin main`
2-	Check the status of files: `git status`
3-	Edit and modify files
4-	Stage the changes (file or files): `git add -A`
5-	Commit the changes: `git commit -m "message …"`
6-	Fetch the latest changes again: `git pull origin main`
7-	Push changes to the repository: `git push origin main`
8-	If a conflict occurs, you will encounter the situation described in step 10
9-	Your code is marked `HEAD`, and your colleague's code is marked `main`
10-	Remove the markers based on which version you decide to keep
11-	Then repeat steps 4, 5, and 7



Second scenario (more professional): Working with a new branch or branch by each person
1- Get the latest version and go to the main branch git checkout main
2- Get the latest changes git pull origin main
3- Create a new branch git checkout -b nameBranch
4- Edit and change files
5- Add changes to the file or files git add -A
6- Record changes git commit -m "message ..."
7- Send the branch to the repository git push origin nameBranch
8- Update the main branch neck to avoid conflict with command number 9
9- git checkout main and then git pull origin main
10- Bring the main main branch into the new branch created with command number 11
11- git checkout nameBranch and then git merge main
12- If a conflict occurs, you will see the two states mentioned in 13
13- Your code >>>>>> HEAD and the collaborator's code >>>>>> main
14- Remove the marks depending on which you decide to keep
15- Steps 5 and Repeat 6
16- Merge the new branch with the original branch with command number 17
17- git checkout main and then git merge nameBranch
18- Final push to GitHub repository git push origin main








