Creating a professional tag (Annotated Tag) ✅ Suggested:
View commits (to select the tag location) git log --oneline
1. git tag -a v1.0.0 -m "First stable release" Suitable for official project versions
2. git tag -a v1.0.0 1a2b3c4(hash or code) -m "First stable release" For a specific commit
3. View the list of tags git tag
4. View tag information git show v1.0.0
5. Send the tag to GitHub individually git push origin v1.0.0
6. Then git push
7. Send all tags to GitHub git push origin --tags
8. Delete the tag locally git tag -d v1.0.0
9. Delete the tag from GitHub git push origin --delete v1.0.0
10. Note: Semantic Versioning is usually used: vMAJOR.MINOR.PATCH
11. Example for 9: v1.0.0 Main version, v1.1.0 Added feature, v1.1.1 Bug fix
🧠 Standard release procedure: 
1. git add .
2. git commit -m "Prepare release v1.0.0"
3. git tag -a v1.0.0 -m "Release version 1.0.0"
4. git push origin main
5. git push origin v1.0.0

